---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Affiliate disclosure — WrenchStack"
  description="How WrenchStack makes money, which programs we participate in, and how affiliate relationships affect (or don't affect) our content."
>
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 prose prose-slate">
    <h1>Affiliate disclosure</h1>

    <p>
      WrenchStack is a participant in affiliate programs operated by the software vendors
      we review. When you click an affiliate link on our site and complete a qualifying
      action (free trial signup, paid plan signup, booked demo), the vendor pays us a
      commission. You pay nothing extra — the commission comes from the vendor's customer
      acquisition budget, not from a price markup on you.
    </p>

    <h2>Programs we currently participate in</h2>

    <p>
      This list is current as of our last review. Specific programs come and go; the list
      is published here in good faith.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>Jobber (direct program)</li>
      <li>Housecall Pro (via PartnerStack)</li>
      <li>ServiceTitan (referral partner program)</li>
      <li>Workiz (direct program)</li>
      <li>BuildOps (direct program)</li>
      <li>Knowify (direct program)</li>
      <li>Service Fusion (direct program)</li>
      <li>Connecteam (via PartnerStack)</li>
      <li>Buildertrend (refer-a-builder)</li>
      <li>FieldEdge (referral partner program)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How affiliate relationships affect content</h2>

    <p>
      Rankings on WrenchStack are produced by an algorithm that has no knowledge of which
      tools pay us or how much. The algorithm considers four equal-weighted factors:
      user ratings, pricing transparency, integration depth, and feature coverage for the
      tool's declared use case. See our <a href="/methodology/">methodology page</a> for
      details.
    </p>

    <p>
      Editorial content (reviews, comparisons, buyer's guides) is written based on public
      product information and aggregated user data — never paid placement. Vendors do
      <em>not</em> review drafts before publication. We sometimes publish criticisms of
      tools we're affiliated with when the data supports it.
    </p>

    <h2>What we don't do</h2>

    <ul>
      <li>We don't accept paid sponsorships, "featured tool" placements, or pay-for-rank arrangements.</li>
      <li>We don't fabricate user reviews or testimonials.</li>
      <li>We don't hide our affiliate links — they're labeled <code>rel="sponsored"</code> in the page source and flagged with disclosure text near every CTA.</li>
      <li>We don't write content "for SEO" that lies about a product.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FTC compliance</h2>

    <p>
      WrenchStack complies with the FTC's <a href="https://www.ftc.gov/business-guidance/resources/disclosures-101-social-media-influencers">Endorsement Guides</a>.
      Affiliate relationships are disclosed on every page that contains affiliate links,
      not just this page.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions?</h2>

    <p>
      If something in our disclosure or methodology looks unclear or off, tell us at{' '}
      <a href="mailto:hello@wrenchstack.com">hello@wrenchstack.com</a>. We will either fix it or
      explain why we don't think it needs fixing. See our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> for
      the right inbox for partnership inquiries vs corrections vs press.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>
